                            only accept IELTS General Training. Always verify you're booking the correct test.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 bg-red-50 p-4 rounded-r-xl mb-4">
                        <div class="font-bold text-red-800 mb-1">Using CELPIP-LS Instead of CELPIP General</div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-red-700">
                            CELPIP-LS (Listening and Speaking only) is not accepted. You must take the full
                            CELPIP General test with all four components.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 bg-red-50 p-4 rounded-r-xl">
                        <div class="font-bold text-red-800 mb-1">Taking Non-Designated Tests</div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-red-700">
                            Only tests from IRCC-designated testing organizations are accepted. Tests like
                            TOEFL, Duolingo, or Cambridge English are not valid for Canadian immigration.
                        </p>
